name: Save checkboxes
func:
let P = msg.payload

// Save Checkboxes

flow.set("cb_ff", P.cb_ff)

flow.set("cb_fd", P.cb_fd)
flow.set("cb_rf", P.cb_rf)
flow.set("cb_rd", P.cb_rd)

flow.set("cb_network", P.cb_network)
flow.set("cb_attached", P.cb_attached)


// rules and facts must be from either files or db
msg.payload = (P.cb_ff || P.cb_fd) && (P.cb_rf || P.cb_rd)

return msg

name: Send to log the output of the results
func:
let messages = []

let P = msg.payload
P.rules.valid.map(p=> messages.push({ruleId: p.id, message: p.message}))


msg.payload = {
    wflid: msg.payload.workflowId,
    passed: msg.payload.rules.valid.length,

    failed: msg.payload.rules.invalid.length,
    messages,
    startTime: flow.get("startTime"),
    endTime: new Date().toLocaleString()

}
msg.topic = "QBES Output"
return msg;
